      "writtenOn": "2021-02-20T13:07:55Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027ve landed the \u003d 0, \u003d 1, part of this.\nhttps://skia-review.googlesource.com/c/skia/+/372976\n\nSkia has learned the painful lesson to not have enum values that are not actually legal. Hence our pattern to have something like kLastValue, but not kCountValues.\n\nenum Foo {\n    A, B, C,\n\n    kLast \u003d C,  // this is fine\n    kCount,     // this is problematic\n};\n\nIf we have an API that takes a Foo, the above would make it legal to pass kCount...\n\nsetFilterQuality(kCount)\n\nObviously, setFilterQuality does not want to have a switch case for kCount, since that is not really one of its \u0027values\u0027.",
      "revId": "146839ab10149d55e22eabd238df6abc74e2ce49",
